<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The type material has not been located (possibly in Paris). Nylander had a very wide circumscription for 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. integra" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="integra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. integra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens identified by Nylander as 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. integra" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="integra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. integra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in H-NYL represent several species of 
<taxonomicName class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the identity of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. integra" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="integra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. integra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be solved without studying the type material. Two old records of this species have been reported from Finland (Vainio 1921), but these specimens belong to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. viridula" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Vainio’s">Vainio's</normalizedToken>
interpretation of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. integra" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="integra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. integra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species may be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. viridula" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
